Argentine Stocks: Mirgor, Siderar SAIC and YPF SA Advance

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-09-20T20:59:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/argentine-stocks-mirgor-sacifia-and-siderar-saic-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index closed little changed at 2,717.15.  Siderar SAIC (ERAR)   gained 1.7 percent to 24.4 pesos,
the biggest gain in a week. The country’s largest steel producer
has called a shareholder meeting for Nov. 10 to vote on the
transfer of 4.2 billion pesos ($1 billion) in unpaid dividends
to the company’s equity account and the issuance of 4.2 billion
new shares, according to a statement posted late yesterday on
the website of the Buenos Aires stock exchange.  Mirgor SACIFIA (MIRG AF) rose 1.1 percent to 96.5 pesos.
The Argentine producer of automobile air conditioning systems
will sell up to 2 million pesos in new class A, B and C shares
worth 0.1 pesos each, according to a statement posted on the
website of the Buenos Aires stock exchange.  YPF SA (YPFD)  , Argentina’s largest oil producer, rose
3.2 percent to 179.5 pesos, its highest price in seven weeks.
Crude oil prices rose today for the first time in three days on
speculation the  Federal Reserve  will take steps to bolster the
 U.S. economy .  To contact the reporter on this story:
